 ## [Unreleased]
 
+Merged to `main` but not yet folded into a tagged release. These harden the
+token economy, the Polar billing webhook, the AI routes, and the insight maths.
+
+### Security
+
+- **Fail closed on metering bypass in production.** The unmetered free-pass
+  (`TOKENS_BYPASS=1`, unconfigured auth, or no DB driver) is now honored only
+  outside production; in production those same conditions resolve to **deny**
+  (HTTP 401), so a single env slip can no longer turn an AI route into an open,
+  anonymous, unmetered billable LLM proxy. Dev/keyless/test behavior unchanged.
+- **Allowlist `CLAUDE_CLI_EXTRA_ARGS` before spawn.** The Claude provider used
+  to pass the raw env var straight into `spawn()` (with `shell:true` on Windows);
+  it is now run through an all-or-nothing validator that permits only a small set
+  of known flags with metacharacter-free values, blocking CLI/shell injection
+  from a tampered environment.
+- **Cap the `POST /api/categorize` description at 500 chars.** An oversized,
+  attacker-controlled `description` flowing into the LLM prompt was a
+  cost-amplification / DoS vector; over-length bodies are now rejected with
+  **HTTP 400** (rejected, not truncated, so financial text is never silently cut).
+
+### Fixed
+
+- **Canonical amount validation at `POST /api/categorize`** (ADR 0008). The live
+  HTTP ingestion boundary now runs the same `isValidSignedAmount` check the
+  ledger uses (signed, non-zero, `|amount| <= $1,000,000`, `<= 2` decimals)
+  instead of a loose `Number.isFinite` test, so zero, out-of-range, and sub-cent
+  amounts are rejected with a tightened **HTTP 400** before they reach
+  categorization. Merged to `main` (PR #1, `b6b7131`); not yet in a tagged release.
+- **Reject model categorizations that contradict the amount sign.** A guard now
+  falls back to the deterministic heuristic when the model's debit/credit
+  direction unambiguously disagrees with the signed amount, so a swapped or
+  mis-booked LLM answer can no longer silently corrupt the double-entry books.
+- **Token balance floors at zero on refund clawback.** A refund larger than the
+  remaining balance no longer drives it negative (which had soft-locked the
+  account against all future charges and silently ate the next top-up).
+- **Refunds reverse the actual recorded charge.** Clawbacks now look the original
+  debit up by its ledger ref and refund exactly that magnitude, and recover the
+  buyer + bundle from the recorded purchase when the Polar refund payload omits
+  the checkout metadata — closing a "refund-and-keep-the-tokens" gap.
+- **Polar credit hardening.** Tokens are credited only on the settled `order.paid`
+  event (not the pre-settlement `order.created`), the bundle is resolved by the
+  server-known product first (echoed metadata only as fallback), and a non-empty
+  order id is required as the idempotency key so retries can't double-credit.
+- **Dev token grants are idempotent.** The dev top-up route uses a deterministic
+  ref, so a double-click or replayed request no longer grants tokens repeatedly
+  (dev-only route, still gated to non-prod + `TOKENS_BYPASS=1`).
+- **No negative business valuation.** The wealth-score valuation base is clamped
+  at 0; a loss-making trailing window now shows an honest "Not yet valuable" state
+  instead of a meaningless negative "exit price."
+- **Benchmark uplift annualized from the real data window.** Projected annual
+  savings now scale by `12 / observed months` instead of a flat ×12, so
+  multi-month data is no longer grossly overstated (this figure also feeds the
+  wealth score and the concierge).
+
+### Changed
+
+- **AI provider fallbacks are now observable.** A telemetry seam logs genuine LLM
+  outages (timeout, crash, parse error) with a structured reason while staying
+  quiet on the benign "not configured" keyless path, so a real outage is no
+  longer indistinguishable from the expected deterministic fallback.
+
+## [0.11.0] - 2026-06-02
+
+Backward-compatible feature release scoped to a single additive `feat` (PR #3,
+ADR 0009). Under the pre-1.0 `0.x` policy a feature lands as a **minor** bump;
+numbered `0.11.0` because `0.10.0` is reserved for the in-flight release PR #2.
+
+### Added
+
+- **`roundToCents` half-up cent canonicalization** (ADR 0009). Promotes the
+  half-up "snap a single user-entered USD figure to two decimals" rule out of a
+  private ledger helper into the shared `@/lib/money` kernel, beside `roundMoney`
+  / `addMoney` / `formatMoney`, so any feature can import it from `@/lib/money`.
+  It is deliberately **distinct** from `roundMoney`: `roundToCents` rounds
+  half-UP (toward +∞) to clean one input at the boundary, while `roundMoney` is
+  currency-aware and rounds half-to-EVEN (banker's) for arithmetic over many
+  rows. Pure and side-effect-free; `-0` is normalized to `0`.
+
+## [0.10.0] - 2026-06-01
+
+Backward-compatible feature release. Adds a **metered AI advisor tier**, a
+**multi-environment database abstraction**, a **second LLM engine** (Claude), a
+**local dev-auth mode**, and a **Playwright user-journey e2e suite**. No breaking
+changes since `0.9.0`; under the pre-1.0 `0.x` policy a feature release
+increments the **minor**, so this lands as `0.10.0`. Bump derived from
+`git log v0.9.0..HEAD` (one additive `feat` commit — `6034931`), not guessed.
+
+### Added
+
+- **Metered AI advisor tier** (ADR-0007). Token-charged "live reads" layered on
+  top of the free static cards: `POST /api/insights/{benchmarks,tax-credits,
+  wealth}` narrate the three insight cards, and a grounded ledger Q&A
+  **concierge** (`POST /api/ask`) answers questions about the books. The server
+  owns the dollars and the facts — it grounds each prompt from the ledger and
+  meters the charge; the model only narrates. Every read keeps a deterministic
+  fallback, so unmetered/keyless builds still return results. New surfaces:
+  `ConciergeThread`, narration modules per insight feature, and `lib/ai/
+  ledger-agent.ts`.
+- **Multi-environment database abstraction** (`src/lib/db/`). One Postgres
+  dialect behind a single `getDb()`, with three swappable drivers selected by
+  `DB_DRIVER` (or auto-detected from the environment): **PGlite** (local,
+  file-backed), **pg** via `DATABASE_URL`, and the **Cloud SQL** connector
+  (`INSTANCE_CONNECTION_NAME`). The token ledger and auth were refactored onto
+  `getDb()`. Schema is bootstrapped from the first migration
+  (`migrations/0001_init.sql`) via new `npm run db:setup` / `db:reset` scripts.
+- **Second LLM engine — Claude Code CLI** behind `LLM_PROVIDER`. A
+  provider-agnostic `generateText` seam (`src/lib/ai/`) chooses the engine:
+  `gemini` (default, the Google SDK + `GEMINI_API_KEY`) or `claude` (the Claude
+  Code CLI in headless mode on a local Pro/Max **subscription** — no API key;
+  local dev only). All AI routes — categorize, the insight reads, and the
+  concierge — now tag provider-honest provenance (`gemini` / `claude` /
+  `fallback`). Providers are dynamically imported so only the active engine's
+  deps load. `CLAUDE_MODEL` / `CLAUDE_CLI_BIN` / `CLAUDE_CLI_TIMEOUT_MS` /
+  `CLAUDE_CLI_EXTRA_ARGS` tune the Claude path.
+- **Local dev-auth mode** (`DEV_AUTH`). Loosens auth to a fixed dev user (no
+  Google OAuth) while keeping **real** token metering locally via PGlite, so the
+  paywall can be exercised end-to-end without cloud infra. New
+  `.env.local.example` and a `docs/SETUP.md` runbook (DB drivers, the Claude
+  provider, dev-auth, Polar product setup via `npm run polar:setup`).
+- **Playwright user-journey e2e suite** driving the real stack (dev-auth +
+  PGlite + Claude): landing, dashboard, metered insight reads, concierge,
+  billing/FAQ, and the paywall (`e2e/01-landing` … `e2e/zz-paywall`, plus shared
+  `helpers.ts`).
+
+### Fixed
+
+- **Wealth-score deep-import.** `wealth-score/lib/compute` imported the
+  `@/features/benchmarks` barrel, pulling the component graph (`next/link`) into
+  an otherwise pure module; switched to a deep import so the pure module stays
+  dependency-light.
+
